name: Julio Foolio
summary: Jacksonville rapper Julio Foolio has been tragically killed in an ambush shooting in Tampa, Florida. The shooting, which occurred across from the University of South Florida while Foolio was celebrating his 26th birthday, has left three others injured. Foolio's passing has been confirmed by his attorney and has sent shockwaves through the music industry. The incident is being investigated as an ambush, and the authorities are actively seeking the perpetrator responsible for this senseless act of violence.

name: John Force
summary: NHRA legend John Force was hospitalized after his Funny Car exploded and crashed during a race at the Virginia Motorsports Park. The 75-year-old driver is reported to be alert and responsive, but his injuries are unknown. The incident occurred during the first round of the Virginia Nationals, when Force's engine exploded and sent his car veering off track into the retaining wall. The impact resulted in a massive fire, but safety crews quickly extinguished the flames and extracted Force from the wreckage. Force is widely considered one of the greatest drag racers of all time, holding 16 NHRA Funny Car championships.
